            </span>
            <span id="Contributor_Name_Mod">
            bill roos
            </span>
            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz It was at Fort Chaffee that I met my wife Teresa. She had come out to a dance at the serviceman’s club with a friend. I was working that night at a part time job I had running a pool hall for Special Services, (the entertainment department of the Army) when a buddy came by to tell me about this good looking girl at the dance. Well, business was slow at the pool hall (no customers at all) so I closed it up early and hustled over to see what this girl looked like. When I saw her, I had to agree she was something special, so I asked her to dance.  
            <br />
            </span>
            <div id="boxmodex3" class="clearfix">
                <div class="ChapterVideoDivMod">
                    <div class="ChapterVideoMod">
                        <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/124071541" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <span id="Chapter_Quote_Mod">
                “She was hoping another guy would ask her.”
                </span>
            </div>

            <span id="Second_Paragraph_Mod">
                After that dance I asked her again and again. She was hoping another guy would ask her, but I always seemed to beat him to her. After the dance was over, and the girls were all leaving, I asked her for a date. She accepted. I asked about a day and the time of 7:30pm. She agreed to the day but wanted me to arrive at 7:00pm instead. That was no problem for me and I showed up as agreed. A long time later I learned she had stood up a guy she had previously made a date with for that same night at 7:30pm and decided she would rather go with me than him. I knew the guy as he also worked in the Finance Office. <br /><br />

                And after that we dated pretty regularly. I went home on leave, and when I was home, I was put on quarters to go down for a 90-day temporary duty in an army base in Louisiana, and because I was on leave, and they needed someone right away, they picked this other guy that Teresa stood up. So he ended up going there for 90 days, and after 90 days he didn’t come back, and we found out he had requested permanent duty there. And it turned out the reason he requested that was that he was running an embezzlement scheme, and got caught, and ended up being sentenced to 20 years of hard labor in military prison (which was reduced to ten years from appeal).<br /><br />

                And... that is how it all started. We now have 6 children and 28 grandchildren. See what happens when you check out what a buddy thinks is a great looking girl? 
            </span>

            <!--span id="See_More_Mod"><a href="#" id="restofstory-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
