                </span>
            </div>
            <span id="Second_Paragraph_Mod">
                While I was working there I lived in an apartment with roommates, and my roommate was my best friend, Mary Rita. Another girl we graduated with needed an apartment to live in, so we decided we would let her come and live with us. Her name was June. One day she persuaded me to ride the bus to the service club at Camp Chaffee. They had dances there, so I went with her. And there I met Bill Roos.<br /><br />

                Everyone sat in chairs around the dance floor, and the boys would ask the girls to dance. Bill Roos asked me to dance several times, and I danced with him. Previously I had made a date with another soldier, and I didn’t really want to go, so when Bill Roos asked me for a date on that same night, I asked him if he could come a little bit earlier so I would miss my first date! He did that. It just happened to be someone who worked in his same office, which was kind of embarrassing because of the situation. Somehow, I don’t think he really minded too much that I stood him up.<br /><br />

                I learned how to do that from my friend June, ‘cause several times when someone would knock on our apartment door, it would be someone who had a date with June, and June was not there. She had stood them up! 
            </span>
            
